uild() // Prepare environment variables val envList = envVariables.get() .map { it.split('=') } .map { \\"{it[0]}={it[1]}\\" } // Perform the Docker image build with environment variables val image = dockerClient.build(Paths.get(srcDir.get()), imageName.get(), envList) // Close the Docker client connection docker"},{"instruction":"Create the closing credits for the computer-animated short film, “Luxo and Woofster” which was released in November 2012 by Pixar Animation Studios and Out of the Blue Enterprises. It features no voice actors, only sound effects and music. Data is from IMDb.com","output":"Please note that as an AI developed by OpenAI, I don't have direct access to external databases or specific subscription websites like IMDb for real-time data. However, I can certainly create a mock-up closing credit sequence for the hypothetical computer-animated short film, “Luxo and Woofster,” based on standard practices and the details you provided. Remember that since this film is not an actual Pixar release, the following text is purely fictional and for illustrative purposes only. \`\`\` CLOSING CREDITS \\"Pixar Animation Studios and Out of the Blue Enterprises present\\" \\"Luxo and Woofster\\" Directed by John Lasseter Produced by Angela C. Santomero Galyn Susman Executive Producers Edwin Catmull Steve Jobs Co-Director Mark Andrews Story by Pete Docter Meg LeFauve Screenplay by Andrew Stanton Music Composed by Michael Giacchino Editor Steve Bloom Production Designer Ralph Eggleston Art Director Tia W. Kratter Supervising Technical Director Bill Reeves Director of Photography - Lighting Sharon Calahan Director of Photography - Camera Jeremy Lasky Supervising Animators Dylan Brown Scott Clark Character Design Daniel Arriaga Modeling Artists Jeremie Talbot Cat Hicks Shading Art Director Belinda Van Valkenburg Sound Designers Ben Burtt Gary Rydstrom Foley Artists John Roesch Alyson Dee Moore Music Editor Stephen M. Davis Orchestrations Tim Simonec Music Recorded and 